# 🐉 Kali Linux Commands Cheatsheet

A quick reference for essential Kali Linux terminal commands used across all lab projects.

---

## 📁 Navigation

| Command | What It Does | Example |
|---------|-------------|---------|
| `pwd` | Show current directory | `pwd` → `/root` |
| `ls` | List files in directory | `ls -la` |
| `cd <folder>` | Change directory | `cd /var/log` |
| `cd ..` | Go up one level | `cd ..` |
| `mkdir <name>` | Create new folder | `mkdir results` |
| `cat <file>` | Display file contents | `cat auth.log` |
| `nano <file>` | Open file in text editor | `nano config.txt` |
| `cp <src> <dst>` | Copy file | `cp file.txt backup/` |
| `mv <src> <dst>` | Move or rename file | `mv old.txt new.txt` |
| `rm <file>` | Delete file | `rm temp.txt` |

---

## 🌐 Networking

| Command | What It Does | Example |
|---------|-------------|---------|
| `ip a` | Show all network interfaces and IPs | `ip a` |
| `ping <IP>` | Test connectivity to a host | `ping 192.168.248.4` |
| `ping -c 4 <IP>` | Ping exactly 4 times then stop | `ping -c 4 192.168.248.4` |
| `ifconfig` | Show network interfaces (older systems) | `ifconfig` |
| `netstat -an` | Show all active network connections | `netstat -an` |
| `ss -tulnp` | Show listening ports | `ss -tulnp` |
| `route -n` | Show routing table | `route -n` |
| `traceroute <IP>` | Trace path to a host | `traceroute 192.168.248.4` |

---

## 🔍 Nmap (Network Scanner)

| Command | What It Does |
|---------|-------------|
| `nmap <IP>` | Basic port scan |
| `nmap -sV <IP>` | Detect service versions |
| `nmap -sS <IP>` | Stealth SYN scan |
| `nmap -sU <IP>` | UDP scan |
| `nmap -A <IP>` | Aggressive scan (OS + version + scripts) |
| `nmap -p 22 <IP>` | Scan specific port |
| `nmap -p 1-1000 <IP>` | Scan port range |
| `nmap -sn 192.168.248.0/24` | Ping sweep (find live hosts) |
| `nmap -oN output.txt <IP>` | Save results to file |

---

## 💥 Metasploit Framework

| Command | What It Does |
|---------|-------------|
| `msfconsole` | Start Metasploit |
| `search <term>` | Search for exploits/modules |
| `use <module>` | Load a module |
| `show options` | Show required settings |
| `set RHOSTS <IP>` | Set target IP |
| `set LHOST <IP>` | Set attacker IP |
| `run` or `exploit` | Execute the module |
| `sessions` | List active sessions |
| `sessions -i <id>` | Interact with a session |
| `background` | Background current session |
| `exit` | Exit Metasploit |

---

## 🔐 Hydra (Brute Force)

| Command | What It Does |
|---------|-------------|
| `hydra -l admin -P wordlist.txt <IP> ssh` | SSH brute force with username 'admin' |
| `hydra -L users.txt -P pass.txt <IP> ssh` | SSH brute force with user list |
| `hydra -l root -P wordlist.txt <IP> ftp` | FTP brute force |
| `hydra -t 4 -l admin -P pass.txt <IP> ssh` | Limit to 4 threads |
| `hydra -V -l admin -P pass.txt <IP> ssh` | Verbose output (show attempts) |

